The Provider grants the User a limited, non-exclusive, and non-transferable right to use the EPOP Documents under the terms of this License.


2. Granted Rights

By downloading the EPOP Documents, the User agrees to the terms and conditions set forth below.


3. Permitted Uses

The User is only granted access to the EPOP Document for the uses made necessary for the achievement of text mining for scientific research purposes of public interest in accordance with the European Directive Directive (EU) 2019/790 on the text mining exception. The User is authorized to modify the EPOP Documents for their own text mining research needs.


4. Restrictions

Any other use, including redistribution, commercial use, or modification outside of scientific research, is strictly prohibited. In no event shall the User share the Document with unauthorized parties, tamper the EPOP Documents, engage in behaviors that would lead third parties to believe the User benefits from more rights on the EPOP Documents that s/he actually has.

Upon completion of the research, the User retains none of the rights granted to them, and commits to forfeiting effective detention of the EPOP Documents, by taking every care to delete permanently all copies of the EPOP Documents in their possession, including modified copies.


5. Attribution

The User must attribute the source of the EPOP Documents by mentioning the Provider in any use of the EPOP Documents specifying « EPOP Documents, provided by INRAE and the ESV Platform».


6. Intellectual Property Rights

All elements within the EPOP Documents are protected by intellectual property rights that restrict reuse beyond the scope of this License. The User acknowledges and accepts that these intellectual property rights are not transferred by this license and that any use outside the permitted scope as defined in this License, is strictly prohibited. For additional information regarding these intellectual property rights, please contact the Data Collection Manager at Platform ESV.


7. Liabilities

The EPOP Documents dataset is provided "as is" without any warranty, express or implied. The Provider will not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages resulting from the use or inability to use the EPOP Documents. In no event shall the Provider be liable for any claims, damages, or other liabilities, whether in contract, tort (including negligence), or otherwise, arising out of or in connection with the EPOP Documents.


8. Data Security

The User agrees to implement reasonable security measures to prevent unauthorized access, use, or distribution of the EPOP Documents. This includes but is not limited to, secure storage and restricted access.


9. Retention of Personal Data

Personal data collected in the visitor registry will be retained in compliance with applicable legal provisions. For more information on the general terms of personal data retention and processing, please refer to the General Terms of Use (https://recherche.data.gouv.fr/en/page/general-terms-and-conditions).


